#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:1
msgid "The basics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:3
msgid "An overview on contributing to the _Black_ project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:5
msgid "Technicalities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:7
msgid ""
"Development on the latest version of Python is preferred. You can use any "
"operating system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:10
msgid "First clone the _Black_ repository:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:12
msgid ""
"$ git clone https://github.com/psf/black.git\n"
"$ cd black\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:17
msgid ""
"Then install development dependencies inside a virtual environment of your "
"choice, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:20
msgid ""
"$ python3 -m venv .venv\n"
"$ source .venv/bin/activate # activation for linux and mac\n"
"$ .venv\\Scripts\\activate # activation for windows\n"
"\n"
"(.venv)$ pip install --group dev\n"
"(.venv)$ pip install -e \".[d]\"\n"
"(.venv)$ pre-commit install\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:30
msgid ""
"Before submitting pull requests, run lints and tests with the following "
"commands from the root of the black repo:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:33
msgid ""
"(.venv)$ pre-commit run -a # Linting\n"
"(.venv)$ tox -e py # Unit tests\n"
"(.venv)$ tox -e fuzz # Optional Fuzz testing\n"
"(.venv)$ tox -e run_self # Format Black itself\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:40
msgid "Development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:42
msgid "Further examples of invoking the tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:44
msgid ""
"(.venv)$ tox --parallel=auto # Run all the above in parallel\n"
"(.venv)$ tox -e py314 # Run tests on a specific python version\n"
"(.venv)$ pytest -k <test name> # Run an individual test\n"
"(.venv)$ tox -e py -- --no-cov # Pass arguments to pytest\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:51
msgid "Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:53
msgid ""
"All aspects of the _Black_ style should be tested. Normally, tests should be "
"created as files in the `tests/data/cases` directory. These files consist of "
"up to three parts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:56
msgid ""
"A line that starts with `# flags: ` followed by a set of command-line "
"options. For example, if the line is `# flags: --preview --skip-magic-"
"trailing-comma`, the test case will be run with preview mode on and the "
"magic trailing comma off. The options accepted are mostly a subset of those "
"of _Black_ itself, except for the `--minimum-version=` flag, which should be "
"used when testing a grammar feature that works only in newer versions of "
"Python. This flag ensures that we don't try to validate the AST on older "
"versions and tests that we autodetect the Python version correctly when the "
"feature is used. For the exact flags accepted, see the function "
"`get_flags_parser` in `tests/util.py`. If this line is omitted, the default "
"options are used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:66
msgid "A block of Python code used as input for the formatter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:67
msgid ""
"The line `# output`, followed by the output of _Black_ when run on the "
"previous block. If this is omitted, the test asserts that _Black_ will leave "
"the input code unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:70
msgid ""
"_Black_ has two pytest command-line options affecting test files in `tests/"
"data/` that are split into an input part, and an output part, separated by a "
"line with `# output`. These can be passed to `pytest` through `tox`, or "
"directly into pytest if not using `tox`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:75
msgid "`--print-full-tree`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:77
msgid ""
"Upon a failing test, print the full concrete syntax tree (CST) as it is "
"after processing the input (\"actual\"), and the tree that's yielded after "
"parsing the output (\"expected\"). Note that a test can fail with different "
"output with the same CST. This used to be the default, but now defaults to "
"`False`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:82
msgid "(.venv)$ tox -e py -- --print-full-tree\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:86
msgid "`--print-tree-diff`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:88
msgid ""
"Upon a failing test, print the diff of the trees as described above. This is "
"the default. To turn it off pass `--print-tree-diff=False`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:91
msgid "(.venv)$ tox -e py -- --print-tree-diff=False\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:95
msgid "News / Changelog Requirement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:97
msgid ""
"`Black` has CI that will check for an entry corresponding to your PR in "
"`CHANGES.md`. If you feel this PR does not require a changelog entry please "
"state that in a comment and a maintainer can add a `ci: skip news` label to "
"make the CI pass. Otherwise, please ensure you have a line in the following "
"format added below the appropriate header:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:102
msgid "- `Black` is now more awesome (#X)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:106
msgid ""
"<!---\n"
"The Next PR Number link uses HTML because of a bug in MyST-Parser that "
"double-escapes the ampersand, causing the query parameters to not be "
"processed.\n"
"MyST-Parser issue: https://github.com/executablebooks/MyST-Parser/"
"issues/760\n"
"MyST-Parser stalled fix PR: https://github.com/executablebooks/MyST-Parser/"
"pull/929\n"
"-->\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:112
msgid ""
"Note that X should be your PR number, not issue number! To workout X, please "
"use <a href=\"https://ichard26.github.io/next-pr-number/?"
"owner=psf&name=black\">Next PR Number</a>. This is not perfect but saves a "
"lot of release overhead as now the releaser does not need to go back and "
"workout what to add to the `CHANGES.md` for each release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:112
msgid ""
"<a href=\"https://ichard26.github.io/next-pr-number/?owner=psf&name=black\">"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:112
msgid "</a>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:117
msgid "Style Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:119
msgid ""
"Please familiarize yourself with our [stability policy](labels/stability-"
"policy). Therefore, most style changes must be added to the `--preview` "
"style. Exceptions are fixing crashes or changes that would not affect an "
"already-formatted file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:123
msgid ""
"If a change would affect the advertised code style, please modify the "
"documentation (The _Black_ code style) to reflect that change. Patches that "
"fix unintended bugs in formatting don't need to be mentioned separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:127
msgid ""
"If the change is implemented with the `--preview` flag, please include the "
"change in the Future Style document instead and write the changelog entry "
"under the dedicated \"Preview style\" heading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:131
msgid "Docs Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:133
msgid "If you make changes to docs, you can test they still build locally too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:135
msgid ""
"(.venv)$ pip install --group docs\n"
"(.venv)$ pip install -e \".[d]\"\n"
"(.venv)$ sphinx-build -a -b html -W docs/ docs/_build/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:141
msgid "Hygiene"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:143
msgid ""
"If you're fixing a bug, add a test. Run it first to confirm it fails, then "
"fix the bug, and run the test again to confirm it's really fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:146
msgid ""
"If adding a new feature, add a test. In fact, always add a test. If adding a "
"large feature, please first open an issue to discuss it beforehand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:149
msgid "Finally"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/the_basics.md:151
msgid ""
"Thanks again for your interest in improving the project! You're taking "
"action when most people decide to sit and watch."
msgstr ""
